toolbar.description:
Note: To disable a toolbar item,
copy it to User Preferences and add the
"disabled" key. The following example will disable the uploader button:
{
  "toolbar": [
    {
      "name": "uploader",
      "disabled": true
    }
  ]
}

Toolbar description:

contextMenu.description:
Note: To disable a context menu item,
copy it to User Preferences and add the
"disabled" key. The following example will disable Download item on files:
{
  "contextMenu": [
    {
      "command": "filebrowser:download",
      "selector": ".jp-DirListing-item[data-isdir=\"false\"]",
      "disabled": true
    }
  ]
}

Context menu description:

layout.description:
Overrides default widget position in the application layout
e.g. to position terminals in the right sidebar in multiple documents mode and in the down are in single document mode, {
  "single": { "Terminal": { "area": "down" } },
  "multiple": { "Terminal": { "area": "right" } }
}.

